soc.game
Class ResourceConstants

java.lang.Object
  soc.game.ResourceConstants

public class ResourceConstants
extends java.lang.Object

This is a list of constants for representing types of resources in Settlers of Catan.

Warning: Many pieces of code depend on these values and their count. Clay is first (1), Wood is last (5), Unknown is after wood. Those are the 5 resource types (count==5 or ==6 (unknown) is also assumed). Adding a new resource type would require changes in many places. RobotBrain.estimateResourceRarity is one of many examples. Constants in other places (like PlayerElement.CLAY) have the same hardcoded values.

Before 1.1.08, this was an interface. Changing to a class allowed adding methods such as resName(int).
